interest. In this demonstration, propensity- score matching
estimates of the Catholic school effect for the Catholic
schooled are provided to supplement the estimates obtained
by regression models. Although subject to their own set of
weaknesses, the matching estimates suggest that the
Catholic school effect is the strongest among those
Catholic school students who, according to their observed
characteristics, are least likely to attend Catholic
schools. Four alternative explanations are offered for this
finding, each of which should be pursued in further
research.},
