implicit cosmologies. <b>For Space </b>is essential reading
for anyone interested in space and the spatial turn in the
social sciences and humanities. Serious, and sometimes
irreverent, it is a compelling manifesto: for re-imagining
spaces for these times and facing up to their
challenge.</p>},
